*Document Layers of the TTAO Academy:*
- *Headmaster Master Guide* (this document) — complete system, source-dense, architectural
- *Guide Manual* (forthcoming) — teaching notes, evaluation rubrics, intervention thresholds
- *Student Yearly Roadmaps* (forthcoming) — high-level orientation for each year
- *Student Monthly Syllabi* (forthcoming) — required practices, readings, lab work, deliverables, and completion thresholds for each month
- *Safety & Ethics Appendices* (see Appendix E) — standalone safety documents, contraindications, community conduct

== Pacing — Competency-Based, Not Calendar-Based

TTAO is competency-paced, not calendar-paced. The three-year structure is a
pedagogical framework and suggested rhythm, not a deadline. A student may take
three years to complete Year One. Advancement is determined by demonstrated
integration and operative attainment — not by elapsed time.

*The primary competency test for Year One is the formation of a verified Plant Stone.*
If the Stone is not formed, the student shares their notes with the headmaster or
guide, identifies areas of weakness or misunderstanding, and continues the relevant
work. There is no failure limit.

